analysis: The agent formatted the timeFrame "end" parameter incorrectly, using "2022-04-15T23:59:59Z" instead of the expected "2022-04-15T00:00:00", causing a mismatch with the expected function call signature and resulting in the evaluator error.

The agent only made two function calls, each combining a different model with a different forecast period, instead of making four calls to cover all model and forecast period combinations as instructed (both models for both time frames).

The agent incorrectly set the licenseManager timeFrame to a single day ("2025-10-09" to "2025-10-09") instead of the entire year ("2025-01-01" to "2025-12-31"), thus failing to match the expected licensing query for the full year.

The agent output the correct function names and arguments but used "arguments" instead of the expected "parameters" key and did not exactly match the required output schema, causing the evaluator to reject the function calls.

The agent incorrectly set the "complexity" of the writingPrompt tool to "detailed" instead of "advanced" as required, causing a parameter mismatch with the expected function call for CreativeSession_startWritingSession. This led to evaluation failure despite correct function targeting and structure.

The agent added unnecessary "severity" fields to the weather_conditions in the function arguments, whereas the expected parameters only included "condition_type". This parameter mismatch caused the function call to not match the expected signature.

The agent failed to properly close the JSON object for the document_management_store tool call, resulting in invalid JSON syntax that could not be parsed, despite the call content being otherwise correct. This caused execution failure.

The agent incorrectly included actual feedback data in the MarketingCampaign_manageFeedback function call instead of leaving the feedbackData arrays empty as expected, leading to a mismatch with the required function call signature.

The agent incorrectly set the "dateRange" for "military_evaluate_threat_levels" to a single day ("2026-11-16" to "2026-11-16") instead of spanning from the start of 2026 to that date, missing the expected range. This led to a parameter mismatch.

The agent used "United States" instead of "USA" for the "country" parameter in the urban_air_quality_monitor function call, leading to a mismatch with the expected function call format and causing the evaluator to not recognize the call as correct.

The agent incorrectly specified "cardboard boxes" for the packaging material instead of the expected "cardboard," causing a parameter mismatch and preventing the fruit processing function call from matching the expected output.

The agent included extraneous "document_id" fields in the insurance_claim_verification function call's documents list, whereas the expected output only required "document_type" fields, resulting in a mismatch and failed function call matching.

The agent incorrectly included the "interactions" key in the "details" parameter for each function call, whereas only "settlements" and "routes" were expected, causing a parameter mismatch and failure to match the expected calls.

The agent incorrectly assigned a severity of 5 instead of the expected 3 for the "swelling" symptom in the ReptileBiteResponseSystem_evaluateBiteSeverity function call, causing a parameter mismatch and preventing recognition by the evaluator.

The agent incorrectly passed extra themes ("Nihilism", "Absurdism", "Individualism") to PhilosophyCinemaExplorer_findPurposeDrivenFilms instead of restricting to just "Existentialism" as required, causing the function call to not match the expected parameters.
The agent omitted the required "documentTypes": ["passport"] parameter when calling VisaInformationManager_getVisaRequirements, resulting in a function call that did not match the expected format.

The agent incorrectly used the OrganTransplantSimulationTool instead of the required OrganTransplantAssistant, failing to execute the function needed for planning and assisting a real organ transplant surgery with robotic and monitoring features as specified.
The agent called the correct function with appropriate parameters but omitted the required "event_details" field in its arguments, resulting in a mismatch with the expected function call schema.

The agent failed to use the correct vehicleID format ("Car XXX"), provided multiple response actions per vehicle instead of the required single best action, selected incorrect action types (missing emergency_warnings), and outputted wrong effectiveness scores.

The agent incorrectly added "terms" (Deposit and Closing Costs) to the RealEstateBiddingAssistant_startNegotiation function calls, which were not required or supported by the expected function signature, causing a mismatch with the expected parameters.

The agent added unnecessary "terms" parameters to the RealEstateBiddingAssistant_startNegotiation function call and omitted the required "date" parameter in the RealEstateAdvisor_getMortgageDetails call, resulting in mismatched function signatures and failure to match the expected calls.

The agent misrepresented the components' connections in the second circuit by using generic "resistor" labels instead of unique identifiers ("resistor1", "resistor2"), failing to specify parallel connectivity as expected, leading to a mismatch with the required function call parameters.

The agent's function call to football_venue_management used "turf maintenance" (lowercase) in the description instead of "Turf maintenance" (capitalized), causing a mismatch with the expected parameters and leading the evaluator to not recognize the function call as matching.

The agent's second tool call included an extra closing curly brace at the end, resulting in malformed JSON that could not be parsed. This syntax error prevented execution despite otherwise correct function arguments.

The agent omitted the "other_elements": [] field in the initial_composition parameter for both function calls, resulting in a parameter mismatch with the expected function signature and causing the test to fail.

The agent incorrectly set the "intensity" parameter for the reverb effect to 0.9 instead of the expected value of 1, and included unnecessary fields ("apply_time": "real-time") not required by the function signature. This caused a mismatch with the expected function call.

The agent omitted required "timeOfDay" parameters in both function calls, resulting in function signatures that did not match the expected schema and causing evaluator rejection despite correct core parameter values.

The agent incorrectly formatted the "settings" parameter for the HomeLightingControl_manageLightSettings function as a list instead of an object, causing the function call to not match the expected schema. This structural error led to the function call being rejected.

The agent incorrectly formatted the "reason.details" field as an object with "scenario" and "examples" keys, rather than as a list of scenario objects. This schema mismatch caused the function call to not be recognized by the evaluator.

The agent used uppercase values ("Swimming") for the "sport" parameter instead of the expected lowercase ("swimming"), causing parameter mismatch and failed function call matching despite otherwise correct tool selection and arguments.

The agent failed to explicitly set "includeEvents": false for the Colosseum request, resulting in a parameter mismatch with the expected function call format that requires this field to be specified (even if false).

The agent's function call for InheritanceMediationScheduler_scheduleSession used "property division" (lowercase) instead of "Property division" (capitalized) for disputeNature, resulting in a parameter mismatch and failure to match the expected function call.
